description: The TV personality will join judges Allison Holker and Maksim Chmerkovskiy following sexual assault allegations against Lythgoe.
title: JoJo Siwa will replace Nigel Lythgoe as a judge on 'So You Think You Can Dance'

description: The sale of the 40 F-16 fighter jets and upgrades to dozens of other jets became linked to Sweden's accession to NATO, after Turkey had objected.
title: The State Department allows the sale of F-16 jets to Turkey to move forward

description: Gaza's largest remaining hospital in Khan Younis can no longer provide critical medical aid to Palestinians, the medical charity group says.
title: Gaza's largest remaining hospital is near collapse, Doctors Without Borders says

description: Alon Ohel was taken in the early hours of Oct. 7. He is a talented pianist, and his mother believes that music can keep them connected: "It's not the hearing — it's the vibe, it's the energy."
title: Her son was taken by Hamas. She threw him a concert in the hopes he could hear it

description: Prison Reimagined: Presidential Portrait Project is on exhibit at President Lincoln's Cottage in Washington. The work of incarcerated artists challenges U.S. presidents' records on mass incarceration.
title: A prison art show at Lincoln's Cottage critiques presidents' penal law past

description: If polls are not perfect predictors of an incumbent's reelection, is there something else that is? Observers have long sought the True North by which to set their compass and their expectations.
title: Early polls don't always foretell the fate of a first-term president. Does anything?

description: It's not just for weight loss. Patients and doctors alike are having success using the diet for illnesses like bipolar disorder and schizophrenia. And research is taking off.
title: Patients say keto helps with their mental illness. Science is racing to understand why

description: The first 737 Max 9 planes have started flying again after a fuselage panel blew off in midair last week. But industry analysts say Boeing's reputation will take a lot longer to repair.
title: The Boeing 737 Max 9 takes off again, but the company faces more turbulence ahead

description: Holocaust Remembrance Day, Jan. 27, feels different this year because of the Oct. 7 Hamas attack on Israel. More Jews were killed that day than on any single day since the Holocaust.
title: International Holocaust Remembrance Day rings differently this year

description: The town of Jacumba, on the California-Mexico border, has experienced a massive influx of migrants. Unofficial detention camps have popped up throughout the community. Then one day, something changed.
title: A California community sees a dip in immigration. Where have all the people gone?

description: H. Sinno, former lead singer of the pioneering Lebanese rock band Mashrou' Leila, pairs their own history with that of the Metropolitan Museum's Temple of Dendur in their new opera.
title: An ancient Egyptian temple in New York inspires a Lebanese American musician

description: Now in its 33rd year, the Environmental Media Awards might be the most celebrity-studded awards ceremony you've never heard of.
title: Hollywood has been giving out climate change-focused awards for 33 years. Who knew?

description: Russia recruits Nepali men with promises of citizenship and enticing wages. But after news of at least 10 Nepali troops killed, Nepal's government and families want to bring their soldiers home.
title: Nepal wants its men back from Russia's war in Ukraine after deaths on the front

description: Even though two 2020 election workers in Fulton County, Ga., endured an onslaught of threats and harassment following baseless fraud claims, people there are eager to serve as poll workers this year.
title: They watched 2 election workers face abuse, and it's compelling them to serve in 2024

description: Houthi rebels launched a missile Friday at a United States warship patrolling the Gulf of Aden. Early Saturday, U.S. forces conducted a strike against a Houthi anti-ship missile.
title: Yemen Houthi rebels fire a missile at a U.S. warship, escalating Mideast conflict

description: Uncertainty have been spreading since Friday's ruling, blocking the deployment of a U.N.-backed police force, with violence reaching new records as gangs tighten their grip on Haiti's capital.
title: Haitians are desperate after Kenyan court blocks police force deployment

description: A prized statue of Jackie Robinson was stolen from a public park in Kansas, spurring a police search and outrage across the city of Wichita.
title: Jackie Robinson statue was stolen from a Kansas park

description: Wrestling icon Vince McMahon resigned Friday from WWE's parent company the day after a former employee filed a federal lawsuit accusing him and another former executive of serious sexual misconduct.
title: Wrestling icon Vince McMahon resigns from WWE parent company after sex abuse suit
